						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone standing near the Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record in late characters is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka • • • 17, Bhādrapada ba. 1[2].</hi> The cyclic year also is lost. It records a grant of land to a <hi rend="italic">Vaishṇava</hi> pontiff (name lost) for worship and offerings to god <hi rend="bold">Rāmachandradēva.</hi> The river <hi rend="bold">Tuṅgabhadra</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

